<heading id="D0A3E150DD38176D8A80211CDB8FE924" bold="true" box="[151,495,356,383]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B9208A2EDD38176D8A80211CDB8FE924" bold="true" box="[151,495,356,383]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
<taxonomicName id="4C542DBFDD38176D8A80211CDBEAE925" box="[151,394,356,382]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Oragua" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavolineata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9208A2EDD38176D8A80211CDBEAE925" bold="true" box="[151,394,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">Oragua flavolineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2133755DD38176D8B86211DDB8FE924" box="[401,495,357,383]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB563CDD38176D8A8021FFDB15E9FB" blockId="4.[151,495,356,416]" box="[151,373,391,416]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
(
<figureCitation id="136F4AB9DD38176D8A8921FFDB24E9FB" box="[158,324,391,416]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1453,1476]" captionTargetBox="[294,1296,902,1422]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[284,1302,889,1432]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 14. Oragua flavolineata sp. nov. (male). 12, aedeagus, anal tube, and paraphyses, lateral view. 13, apical portion of aedeagus, caudal view. 14, paraphyses, dorsal view. Compare with Figs 6 - 8 of O. linnavuorii sp. nov. AED = aedeagus; ATB = anal tube; PAR = paraphyses. Scale bar: 9 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264863/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
Figures 
<number id="3D9C441BDD38176D8AEC21F0DB24E9FB" box="[251,324,392,416]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" value="13.08" valueMax="14.16" valueMin="12.0">12–14</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136F4AB9DD38176D8B5821FFDB0CE9FB" box="[335,364,391,416]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,263,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[230,1347,211,1205]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,195,1221]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 17. Body in dorsal view (antennae and legs not depicted). 15, male paratype of Oragua linnavuorii sp. nov. (total length 9.9 mm), yellow color of body marks altered due to previous preservation in alcohol. 16, male holotype of O. flavolineata sp. nov. (total length 9.8 mm), slightly laterodorsal. 17, male of Aguana sp. (total length 15.3 mm). The anterior margin of the crown is obtusely rounded in Oragua, whereas it is broadly rounded and truncate medially in Aguana. See discussion for additional differences between the two genera." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264864/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">16</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34E05B7DD38176D8A8021B7DFF4EAC7" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEB563CDD38176D8A8021B7D800E9B3" blockId="4.[151,1436,463,848]" box="[151,608,463,488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
Total length of male: 9.8 mm (
<typeStatus id="54EFE89EDD38176D8BFB21B7D835E9B3" box="[492,597,463,488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">holotype</typeStatus>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB563CDD38176D8AD0218DDB12EA0F" blockId="4.[151,1436,463,848]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C542DBFDD38176D8B6F218CD878EA57" box="[376,536,500,524]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Oragua" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linnavuorii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9208A2EDD38176D8B6F218CD878EA57" box="[376,536,500,524]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">O. linnavuorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9208A2EDD38176D8837218CD81BEA56" bold="true" box="[544,635,500,525]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2133755DD38176D8837218CD81BEA56" box="[544,635,500,525]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
but with apical aedeagal processes (
<figureCitation id="136F4AB9DD38176D8E0D218CDEFCEA57" box="[1050,1180,500,525]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1453,1476]" captionTargetBox="[294,1296,902,1422]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[284,1302,889,1432]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 14. Oragua flavolineata sp. nov. (male). 12, aedeagus, anal tube, and paraphyses, lateral view. 13, apical portion of aedeagus, caudal view. 14, paraphyses, dorsal view. Compare with Figs 6 - 8 of O. linnavuorii sp. nov. AED = aedeagus; ATB = anal tube; PAR = paraphyses. Scale bar: 9 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264863/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
Figs 
<number id="3D9C441BDD38176D8E43218CDEFCEA57" box="[1108,1180,500,524]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" value="12.13">12, 13</number>
</figureCitation>
) distinctly longer and, more importantly, paraphyses (
<figureCitation id="136F4AB9DD38176D8BE1226FD819EA6B" box="[502,633,535,560]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1453,1476]" captionTargetBox="[294,1296,902,1422]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[284,1302,889,1432]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 14. Oragua flavolineata sp. nov. (male). 12, aedeagus, anal tube, and paraphyses, lateral view. 13, apical portion of aedeagus, caudal view. 14, paraphyses, dorsal view. Compare with Figs 6 - 8 of O. linnavuorii sp. nov. AED = aedeagus; ATB = anal tube; PAR = paraphyses. Scale bar: 9 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264863/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
Figs 
<number id="3D9C441BDD38176D88272260D819EA6B" box="[560,633,536,560]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" value="12.14">12, 14</number>
</figureCitation>
) with stalk thick and rami bearing two pairs of short, spiniform apical processes (
<figureCitation id="136F4AB9DD38176D8B062244DB05EA0F" box="[273,357,572,597]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1453,1476]" captionTargetBox="[294,1296,902,1422]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[284,1302,889,1432]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 14. Oragua flavolineata sp. nov. (male). 12, aedeagus, anal tube, and paraphyses, lateral view. 13, apical portion of aedeagus, caudal view. 14, paraphyses, dorsal view. Compare with Figs 6 - 8 of O. linnavuorii sp. nov. AED = aedeagus; ATB = anal tube; PAR = paraphyses. Scale bar: 9 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264863/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9C441BDD38176D8B512244DB05EA0F" box="[326,357,572,596]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB563CDD38176D8AD02227DBF0EA23" blockId="4.[151,1436,463,848]" box="[199,400,607,632]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">Female unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB563CDD38176D8AD022FCDFF4EAC7" blockId="4.[151,1436,463,848]" box="[199,1428,644,669]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis id="B9208A2EDD38176D8AD022FCDBDAEAC6" bold="true" box="[199,442,644,669]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">Known distribution.</emphasis>
Atlantic Forest, Southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F34316ACDD38176D891A22FCD931EAC6" box="[781,849,644,669]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Mantiqueira mountain range), Minas Gerais State.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
