<subSubSection id="C34E05B7DD38176D8AD0236CD8F3EB0B" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEB563CDD38176D8AD0236CDF76EB76" blockId="4.[151,1436,463,848]" box="[199,1302,788,813]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis id="B9208A2EDD38176D8AD0236CDB2EEB76" bold="true" box="[199,334,788,813]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet, 
<taxonomicName id="4C542DBFDD38176D882E236CD8DFEB77" box="[569,703,788,812]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Oragua" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavolineata">
<emphasis id="B9208A2EDD38176D882E236CD8DFEB77" box="[569,703,788,812]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">flavolineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, refers to the color pattern of the forewings (
<figureCitation id="136F4AB9DD38176D8EA2236CDF69EB76" box="[1205,1289,788,813]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,263,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[230,1347,211,1205]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,195,1221]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 17. Body in dorsal view (antennae and legs not depicted). 15, male paratype of Oragua linnavuorii sp. nov. (total length 9.9 mm), yellow color of body marks altered due to previous preservation in alcohol. 16, male holotype of O. flavolineata sp. nov. (total length 9.8 mm), slightly laterodorsal. 17, male of Aguana sp. (total length 15.3 mm). The anterior margin of the crown is obtusely rounded in Oragua, whereas it is broadly rounded and truncate medially in Aguana. See discussion for additional differences between the two genera." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264864/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9C441BDD38176D8EFD236CDF69EB76" box="[1258,1289,788,813]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB563CDD38176D8AD0234FD8F3EB0B" blockId="4.[151,1436,463,848]" box="[199,659,823,848]" pageId="4" pageNumber="426">
